content:
Life Sciences Cloud is a new end-to-end product built on the Salesforce platform for organizations engaged in the Life Sciences industry. It inherits features from Health Cloud and adds its own set of features to optimize operations in clinical, medical, and commercial domains.

Participant Management:
- Criteria-Based Search and Filter (CBSF) helps discover clinical trials.
- OmniStudio components streamline participant application process.
- Stage Management efficiently manages enrollment journey.
- A digital approach eliminates complex paper-based processes for consent capture.

Patient Program Outcome Management (Pilot):
- Optimizes program effectiveness by tracking patient progress.
- Improves patient experience and adherence with tailored assessments.
- Stores calculated response scores to assess outcomes.
- Provides insights to improve case manager efficacy and identify programs that deviate from expected outcomes.

Pharmacy Benefits Verification:
- Empowers agents to quickly gain a comprehensive understanding of pharmacy benefits coverage details.
- Generates a summary of medication benefits within a care program.
- Shares the benefits package with patients, fostering informed decisions about their treatment plans.

Life Sciences Cloud Has New Objects:
- Stores and accesses more data with new objects.

New Invocable Actions in Life Sciences Cloud:
- Sets up randomization process for research study block records and candidate assignments to comparison groups.

New Metadata Types in Life Sciences Cloud:
- Generates research study randomization blocks and randomly assigns candidates to comparison groups.
title: Life Sciences Cloud: New Features and Enhancements
